- Uses regex to find `{{...}}` placeholders
- Uses `Function` constructor (safer than `eval()`) to evaluate expressions with data variables in scope
- Supports simple variables like `{{name}}`
- Supports expressions like `{{age + 1}}`
- Supports property access like `{{items.length}}`
- Returns the original placeholder if evaluation fails
- Converts results to strings for rendering

